usage: uselect [-h] [-s SELECT] [-i] [-m MESSAGE] [-v] [item [item ...]]

uselect is an interactive line filter intended for use in pipelines. Input
lines are read from the command-line or stdin, and displayed to the user.
Selected input lines are written to stdout.

positional arguments:
  item                  read items from command-line rather than stdin

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -s SELECT, --select-regex SELECT
                        select lines matching regex SELECT
  -i, --invert-selection
                        select lines NOT matching regex SELECT
  -m MESSAGE, --message MESSAGE
                        message to display in status bar
  -v, --version         show program's version number and exit

https://github.com/sdt/uselect
